{
  "texts": [
    "In these circumstances, the equation of state parameter is characterized as a function of the universe's scale factor a, such that w = w(a).",
    "To investigate a time-based equation of state, we take up the functional structure as a generic Taylor expansion of w in powers of the scale factor up to order N as follows",
    "Note that, all parameters are unfluctuating when adopting higher order polynomials.",
    "In fact, the w i parameters are limited and going from N = 1 (the linear element) to N = 2 (the quadratic element) to N = 3 (the cubic element) does not better the goodness of fit and its compatibility with ΛCDM is still maintained, which implies that a linear parameterization is enough in this situation.",
    "So, it is logical this series come to a stop at first order in w(a)."
  ]
}